This is a known breaking change. Android deprecated `SOFT_INPUT_ADJUST_RESIZE` (API 30+), and .NET 10 MAUI no longer supports it reliably. The modern fix is to react to **window insets** on Android.

### Recommended approach

**1. In `MainActivity.cs`, enable edge-to-edge and listen for keyboard insets:**

```csharp
using AndroidX.Core.View;

protected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)
{
    base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);

    WindowCompat.SetDecorFitsSystemWindows(Window!, false);

    var content = FindViewById(Android.Resource.Id.Content)!;
    ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(content, new KeyboardInsetsListener());
}

private class KeyboardInsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object, IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener
{
    public WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(Android.Views.View v, WindowInsetsCompat insets)
    {
        var imeInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());
        var navBar   = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.NavigationBars());

        // Push content up by keyboard height (minus nav bar already accounted for)
        v.SetPadding(0, 0, 0, Math.Max(imeInsets.Bottom, navBar.Bottom));
        return insets;
    }
}
```

**2. Structure your XAML so the input bar is at the bottom of a `Grid`:**

```xml
<Grid RowDefinitions="*,Auto">
    <CollectionView Grid.Row="0" ItemsSource="{Binding Messages}" ... />
    <HorizontalStackLayout Grid.Row="1" Padding="8">
        <Entry Placeholder="Type a message..." HorizontalOptions="FillAndExpand" />
        <Button Text="Send" />
    </HorizontalStackLayout>
</Grid>
```

### Why this works

The insets listener detects the IME (keyboard) height and applies bottom padding to the root Android view, pushing your entire MAUI layout up — no platform-specific XAML needed.

### iOS

No changes needed — iOS `KeyboardAutoManagerScroll` handles this automatically in MAUI. If you hit issues, ensure it's not disabled:

```csharp
// MauiProgram.cs — this is ON by default
builder.ConfigureMauiHandlers(h =>
{
    Microsoft.Maui.Platform.KeyboardAutoManagerScroll.Connect = true;
});
```
